        "title": "Resolution",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above This Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Act 3:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The Protagonist begins to resolve their problem with the assistance of new hope, ideas, new/returning Allies, or a personal change – and the action starts to rise once more to the Resolution. A moment of epiphany may serve as another minor complication but ultimately leads to a resolution. The problem's solution leads to a sense of completion or change for the Protagonist. "
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Offer new hope which begins to solve the problem (e.g. the Ally who purchased the replacement ticket remains calm in the face of this new dilemma and begins to look for other options)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Include an epiphany moment (e.g. it is not possible for a direct flight, but they find a series of connecting flights from a different airline which will get the Protagonist to the funeral on time, at an added expense)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Show that problem is resolved and the Protagonist attains their goal (e.g. after trials and tribulations, the Protagonist arrives in Europe just in time to attend the funeral)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Demonstrate how the Protagonist has grown (e.g. The Protagonist learns the value of enlisting the support of others and also learns to stay calm in the face of difficulties, making it easier to find solutions)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Spend time with the Protagonist following their newly attained goal (e.g. they attend the funeral, reminisce with family, and perhaps meet a new love interest or discover something that sparks a new adventure)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 3 makes up the final 25% of the story. "
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The moment of epiphany occurs around the 85% to 90% mark."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Resolution brings the story to its conclusion."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
