      {
        "id": 1,
        "lineId": 1,
        "beatId": 2,
        "bookId": null,
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInBeat": 0,
        "title": "Trigger Event",
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "--- Add Your Details Above This Line ---"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Beginning of Act 1:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Begin your story with the setup in the Protagonist's ordinary world, leading to the Triggering Event, an external event that sets the story in motion. This could be discovering new knowledge, a job loss, a birth/death, a trip, or an invitation to adventure. It must be a critical event for the story, which introduces a problem that interferes with the character's goal and increases drama, bringing the story to its first low point."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Begin the story in the ordinary world and introduce the Protagonist (e.g. they live in Canada and work a mid-range job)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Choose the most important event from the series of events in the story to launch it (e.g. the Protagonist needs to fly to Europe for the funeral of a close family member)."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Set up a problem to begin lowering the action and increasing drama. This will bring the story to the 1st Turning Point (e.g. the Protagonist needs to leave for their flight but cannot find their tickets)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Breakdown:",
                "bold": true
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "bulleted-list",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Act 1 makes up the first 25% of the story."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "The Trigger Event should occur approximately around the 10% mark."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "list-item",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "This entire section should bring the story approximately to the 25% mark."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
